channel.title: Forum Member of the Week - 24 SanaB :sb:
channel.description:
![SB|544x101](upload://lxhYybBxNvLONeAhSQXoxDYAddm.jpg)
<big> Featured Auxy Artist #24: @anon73773654 </big>
<big>S</big>anaB (Previously FroYo) is an American producer and a regular contributor to this forum, where shes consistently supported the featured artists.
Her first EP "[Excursion](https://soundcloud.com/sanabmusic/sets/excursion)" was released in May on Spotify, Soundcloud, iTunes, Google Play and Amazon. It's worth a listen and includes tracks featuring @Goxenar & Hayvn. [[Fan Link](https://sanab.fanlink.to/excursion)]
**Which instruments do you play?** Clarinet to an advanced level and Ukelele. She'd like to see soft electric guitars in Auxy: - "Not the heavy rock kind (because almost no one here will benefit from that :stuck_out_tongue_winking_eye: :stuck_out_tongue_winking_eye: ) but the calming kind that can be used in chill music."
**Who is your fav Auxy producer?** "Every awesome person who makes Auxy… so basically everyone here."
**Week starting: 11 June, 2018.** - Please listen to at least one :sb: track (or more) - Provide at least one Soundcloud comment / feedback about her music during their week. - Comment in this thread once you've provided any feedback. - If you want to be featured, remember to comment for others!
Check out her tracks here: :soundcloud: https://soundcloud.com/sanabmusic/tracks Or listen to the [Excursion EP](https://soundcloud.com/sanabmusic/sets/excursion)
Visit the [SanaB website](https://sanabmusic.wixsite.com/sanab)
If you want to be in the weekly draw [add your name.](https://disco.auxy.co/t/forum-member-of-the-week-who-wants-to-be-involved/5518)

item.title: Forum Member of the Week - 24 SanaB :sb:
item.dc:creator: MisterMaster
item.description:
I totally agree with the feedback above: - The quality of your music has clearly improved & you’re a well-liked, positive part of our community.

You’ve found your niche, with chilled tracks and understated drums. And you’ve done some awesome collabs.

My fav tracks:

  • Tranquility (Ft Haven) - This is my overall fav. Leaving room for a vocal requires a whole different approach to laying out the track. You two smashed it.

  • Excursion (Ft Goxenar) - Sweet guitar strumming into. Can see the improvement from the strumming in Tides, with more varied and interesting layering, automation and pacing.

  • Perception and Amethyst (with Cosmic Superior) - Both are chilled out, nicely understated and easy listening.

  • Alleviate - Love the intro. And the way you didn’t just keep adding instruments; You just included what was needed. Nice restraint.

Thanks for being our 24th Forum Member of the Week SanaB! It’s good to have you here.

Read full topic

item.description:
@anon73773654
First of all, you’re legendary . I’m really impressed by how much you’ve improved over the last few months, your tracks are quality and keep getting better. I’m a big fan of your use of drums and percussion in all your tracks, they really add to the structure of your tracks. In terms of genres, I really like the more poppy stuff you make, such as Tranquility with HAYVN, which is great, as well as your latest deep house track Perception, which is probably my favorite track of yours, it’s fire . You should definitely continue experimenting with genres, it has worked out really well for you .
I’m really curious where your style will go, keep it up!
